FT Map Screen Saver
==================

A lightweight Windows 10/11 screen saver that recreates the classic "defrag disk map" animation vibe.

**Visual only** it does **not** access, analyze, or defragment your disks.

Contents
--------
- Introduction
- Build
- Run / Install
- Tweak Colors & Balance
- License

Introduction
------------
- WinForms / .NET 8 (`net8.0-windows`)
- Full-screen on all monitors
- Exits on mouse/keyboard activity (like a normal screen saver)

Build
-----
Requirements: .NET 8 SDK

Fast build:
- Run `build.cmd`
- Output: `dist\FTMapScreenSaver.scr`

Run / Install
-------------
Run:
- `dist\FTMapScreenSaver.scr /s`   (screen saver)
- `dist\FTMapScreenSaver.scr /c`   (config dialog)
- `dist\FTMapScreenSaver.scr /p <HWND>` (preview; Windows calls this)

Install:
- Right-click the `.scr` → **Install**
  (or copy it to `C:\Windows\System32\` if you prefer the old-school way)

Tweak Colors & Balance
----------------------
- Palette (colors): `DiskMapSimulator.cs` → `DiskMapPalette`
- Distribution (how much red/black/green you see): `GenerateInitialMap()` weights and segment counts

